text: The Rachel Kilpatrick Purdy House is a historic house in Beatrice, Nebraska. It was built in 1915 for Rachel Kilpatrick as a wedding gift from her father, and designed in the Prairie School style by architect Richard W. Grant. Nine photos from 2005 which were part of the nomination are not included in the document. It remained in the Kilpatrick family until 1925. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since November 8, 2006. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Gage County, Nebraska Category:Prairie School architecture in Nebraska Category:Houses completed in 1915 Category:1915 establishments in Nebraska
